main event: Witnesses in Grand Haven, Michigan reported sightings of an unidentified flying object on February 27, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed to have a patch of blue-green light on its lower left quadrant., Multiple witnesses reported seeing the object making sudden movements and disappearing suddenly., Witnesses calculated the size of the object to be comparable to a one-story house at the observed distance., The investigation suggested the object was not Venus, but the true nature of the object remains unidentified., There were reports comparing the brightness of the object to that of Venus, but witnesses noted it was much brighter and more striking.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object with a blue-green light
witness description: Various individuals from the Ottawa County area, including locals and officials from the Grand Haven and Muskegon County Airports.
